---

## 5. Hackathon Strategy: How to Win

1.  **The "Live" Factor:** During the demo, show **Real GitHub Data**. It proves the tech is real. Then switch to the simulated "LinkedIn" data for the complex social graph.
2.  **Focus on "Why Now":** Judges see "Connect" buttons all the time. They rarely see a **"Do NOT Connect (Wait 2 Days)"** button. Highlight this feature—it shows deep thoughtfulness.
3.  **Visuals Over Text:** The **Force-Directed Graph** (The Web) must be the centerpiece. It looks complex, technical, and impressive on a projector.

---

## 6. Appendix: Data Structure (JSON Schema)
*Use this structure for all simulated data to ensure the Graph and AI can read it.*

```json
{
  "user_id": "target_001",
  "name": "Dr. Rohit Verma",
  "role": "Senior Researcher @ DeepMind",
  "alumni_status": "BITS Pilani (2018)",
  "connection_path": ["You", "Prof. S. Rao", "Dr. Rohit Verma"],
  "momentum_metrics": {
    "last_active": "2 hours ago",
    "activity_volume_7d": "High",
    "sentiment": "Frustrated"
  },
  "recent_context": [
    {"source": "GitHub", "event": "Push", "repo": "alpha-fold-3", "timestamp": "2026-01-16T14:30:00"},
    {"source": "Twitter", "event": "Post", "text": "Struggling with GPU allocation today.", "timestamp": "2026-01-16T15:00:00"}
  ]
}
```
